<span id="freeTextContainer13202826157680614">In this installment, Mrs. Pollifax has a somewhat meatier assignment than her previous ones. In the past, she has just been a courier and photographer. This time, she is sent to China with a tour group and tasked with finding a certain person and getting him to give her the location of a labor camp. There is a person of interest there who the CIA would like to rescue. She is not to complete the rescue, just get the location. Another agent will take over from there. The only problem is, the USSR </span>
  <span id="freeText13202826157680614" style="display:none">In this installment, Mrs. Pollifax has a somewhat meatier assignment than her previous ones. In the past, she has just been a courier and photographer. This time, she is sent to China with a tour group and tasked with finding a certain person and getting him to give her the location of a labor camp. There is a person of interest there who the CIA would like to rescue. She is not to complete the rescue, just get the location. Another agent will take over from there. The only problem is, the USSR is also interested in the prisoner...<br /><br />I enjoyed the China travelogue aspect of this one. It also had fewer "yeah, right" moments, at least for me. I also liked the addition of another agent in this one. It was nice to see Mrs. Pollifax interacting with him.</span>
