  <span id="freeText6977314385596550548" style="display:none">The sixth book in this cozy mystery series was written while the Cold War was ongoing and China was emerging from isolation. I liked the characters, the mystery behind the operation, and the descriptions. One situation was quite jarring for me, but then the series does have some dependence on Mrs. Pollifax's good luck. <br /><br />You'll need to have read the earlier books in the series to fully enjoy this one. I knocked it down a half star for the jarring situation. I'm rounding it down because of an unlikely coincidence. </span>
