<div id="review_2755739076" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2755739076" />
    <a title="Deanna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25852459-deanna"><img alt="Deanna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499282473p2/25852459.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2755739076?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deanna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deanna" href="/user/show/25852459-deanna">Deanna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2755739076" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2979905318663569871">A few years ago I stumbled on this series and found it unique, amusing enough, a satisfying source of light reading. Returning to dip back into the series, I found it predictable after the earlier reads and, while not objectionable, no longer satisfying. It seems I moved on in between reads. </span>

