        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3453857783" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5309438679553792445"> I love Mrs. Pollifax! --- Her attitude is wonderfully upbeat and unique. OK – she is quite unbelievable. She’s a grandmother and a CIA Agent who knows karate… but reading of her adventures is a great getaway for the mind. The hardest thing to do is to stop your mind from telling you that “this could never happen that way” or “it is impossible for her to do that” ---- Yes, probably both of those things are true, but just don’t pay any attention to your common sense and relax and enjoy the story.</span>
  <span id="freeText5309438679553792445" style="display:none"> I love Mrs. Pollifax! --- Her attitude is wonderfully upbeat and unique. OK – she is quite unbelievable. She’s a grandmother and a CIA Agent who knows karate… but reading of her adventures is a great getaway for the mind. The hardest thing to do is to stop your mind from telling you that “this could never happen that way” or “it is impossible for her to do that” ---- Yes, probably both of those things are true, but just don’t pay any attention to your common sense and relax and enjoy the story. ----This is one of the best of the Mrs. Pollifax adventures – and it doesn’t strain your credulity quite as far as some of the other novels. All she has to do go on a tour of the remote NW part of Communist China, find a secret relocation (prisoner) camp, and help someone escape with no backup to help her.—Piece of cake!</span>
  <a data-text-id="5309438679553792445" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
